body:
UNGELD. In Saxon law. An outlaw;
a person whose murder required no composition to be made, or weregeld to be paid, by
his slayer.

USUAL. Habitual; ordinary; customary ;
according to usage or custom; commonly established, observed, or practised. See Chicago & A. R. Co. v. Hauser, 71 Ill. App. 147;
Kellogg v. Curtis, 69 Me. 214, 81 Am. Rep.
273; Tischer v. Merica, 118 Ind. 586, 21 N.

UTAS.
the octave;
term or feast.
